     some characters (by default â€˜,â€™ â€˜;â€™ â€˜)â€™ â€˜}â€™ â€˜]â€™) may trigger auto
     reindentation under appropriate conditions.  See the documentation
     of â€˜haskell-indentation-common-electric-commandâ€™ for more details.

   â€¢ â€˜haskell-indent-modeâ€™ (optional).

     This is a semi-intelligent indentation mode doing a decent job at
